<h2 align="center">Decentralized Software Evolution</h2>

<dl>
    <dd><p align="left">Peyman Oreizy. &quot;<strong>Decentralized
        Software Evolution&quot;</strong>. <em>Proceedings of the
        </em><a href="http://kt-www.jaist.ac.jp:8000/icse98.html"><em>International
        Conference on the Principles of Software Evolution (IWPSE
        1)</em></a>. Kyoto, Japan. April 20-21, 1998.<br>
        Available in <a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~peymano/papers/iwpse98.ps">postscript</a>,
        <a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~peymano/papers/iwpse98.pdf">Acrobat
        PDF</a>, and <a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~peymano/papers/iwpse98/">HTML</a>.
        The <a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~peymano/papers/iwpse98/slides/">presentation
        slides</a> are also available.</p>
    </dd>
</dl>

<dl>
    <dd><p align="left">Peyman Oreizy and Richard N. Taylor.
        &quot;<strong>Coping with Application Inconsistency in
        Decentralized Software Evolution&quot;</strong>. <em>Proceedings
        of the </em><a
        href="http://dontaku.csce.kyushu-u.ac.jp/IWPSE99/"><em>Second
        International Conference on the Principles of Software
        Evolution (IWPSE 2)</em></a>. Fukuoka, Japan. July 16-17,
        1999.<br>
        Available in <a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~peymano/papers/iwpse99.pdf">Acrobat
        PDF</a>.</p>
</dl>

<h2 align="center">Software Architecture</h2>

<h3>Runtime System Evolution</h3>

<dl>
    <dd>Peyman Oreizy, Michael M. Gorlick, Richard N. Taylor,
        Dennis Heimbigner, Gregory Johnson, Nenad Medvidovic,
        Alex Quilici, David S. Rosenblum, and Alexander L. Wolf.
        &quot;<font size="2" face="arial,helvetica,geneva"><b>An
        Architecture-Based Approach to Self-Adaptive Software</b></font>,&quot;
        <em>IEEE Intelligent Systems, </em>vol. 14, no. 3, pages
        54-62. May/June 1999.&nbsp;A revised version of <em>UCI-ICS
        Technical Report 98-27</em>, Department of Information
        and Computer Science, University of California, Irvine,
        August 1998.<br>
        Available in <a href="ieee-is99.pdf">Acrobat PDF</a>. The
        article appeared in a <a
        href="http://www.computer.org/intelligent/ex1999/x3toc.htm">special
        issue</a> on Self-adaptive software.</dd>
    <dt>&nbsp;</dt>
    <dd>Peyman Oreizy. &quot;<strong>Issues in Modeling and
        Analyzing Dynamic Software Architectures&quot;. </strong><em>Proceedings
        of the </em><a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~djr/rosatea/"><em>International
        Workshop on the Role of Software Architecture in Testing
        and Analysis</em></a>, Marsala, Sicily, Italy. June 30 -
        July 3, 1998.<br>
        Available in <a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~djr/rosatea/papers/oreizy.pdf">Acrobat
        PDF</a>. </dd>
    <dt>&nbsp;</dt>
    <dd>Peyman Oreizy, Richard N. Taylor. &quot;<strong>On the
        role of software architectures in runtime system
        reconfiguration</strong>&quot;. <em>IEE Proceedings&#151;Software</em>,
        vol. 145, no. 5, October 1998. This paper is a revised
        version of the ICCDS'98 paper below.<br>
        Available in <a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~peymano/papers/iee98.pdf">Acrobat
        PDF</a>. </dd>
    <dd>&nbsp;</dd>
    <dd>Peyman Oreizy, Richard N. Taylor. &quot;<strong>On the
        Role of Software Architectures in Runtime System
        Reconfiguration</strong>&quot;. <em>Proceedings of the Fourth
        International Conference on Configurable Distributed
        Systems (ICCDS 4)</em>, pages 61-70, Annapolis,
        Maryland, May 4-6, 1998.<br>
        Available in <a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~peymano/papers/iccds98.ps">postscript</a>
        and <a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~peymano/papers/iccds98.pdf">Acrobat
        PDF</a>.</dd>
    <dt>&nbsp;</dt>
    <dd>Peyman Oreizy, Nenad Medvidovic, Richard N. Taylor.
        &quot;<b>Architecture-Based Runtime Software Evolution</b>&quot;<b>.
        </b><em>Proceedings of the </em><a
        href="http://icse98.aist-nara.ac.jp/"><em>International
