<h3>Reuse and Architectural Style</h3>

<dl>
    <dd>Nenad Medvidovic, Peyman Oreizy, and Richard N. Taylor.
        &quot;<b>Reuse of Off-the-Shelf Components in C2-Style
        Architectures</b>&quot;.<a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~peymano/papers/SSR97.ps"> </a><i>Proceedings
        of the 1997
        Symposium on Software Reusability (SSR'97)</i>, pages
        190-198, Boston, MA, May 17-19, 1997. Reprinted in <em>Proceedings
        of the 1997 International Conference on Software
        Engineering (ICSE'97)</em>, pages 692-700, Boston, MA,
        May 17-23, 1997. Also reprinted in <em>Software
        Engineering Notes</em>, vol. 22, no. 3, pages 190-198.<br>
        Available in <a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~peymano/papers/SSR97.ps">postscript</a>
        and <a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~peymano/papers/SSR97.pdf">Acrobat
        PDF</a>.</dd>
</dl>

<h3>Architectural Style and Modeling</h3>

<dl>
    <dd>Richard N. Taylor, Nenad Medvidovic, Kenneth M. Anderson,
        E. James Whitehead, Jr., Jason E. Robbins, Kari A. Nies,
        Peyman Oreizy, and Deborah L. Dubrow. &quot;<b>A
        Component- and Message-Based Architectural Style for GUI
        Software</b>&quot;. <i>IEEE Transactions on Software
        Engineering</i>, vol. 22, no. 6, pages 390-406, June 1996.
        <br>
        Available in <a
        href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/pub/arch/papers/copyright-IEEE.html">postscript</a>.</dd>
</dl>

<dl>
    <dd>Nenad Medvidovic, Peyman Oreizy, Jason E. Robbins, and
        Richard N. Taylor. &quot;<b>Using Object-Oriented Typing
        to Support Architectural Design in the C2 Style</b>&quot;.
        Proceedings of the<i> Fourth ACM SIGSOFT Symposium on the
        Foundations of Software Engineering (FSE4)</i>, pages 24-32,
        San Francisco, CA, October 16-18, 1996. Reprinted in <em>Software
        Engineering Notes</em>, vol. 21, no. 6, pages 24-32,
        November 1996. Also available as <em>UCI Technical Report
        96-6</em>. <br>
        Available in <a
        href="ftp://liege.ics.uci.edu/pub/arcadia/c2/C2-FSE96.fm.ps">postscript</a>.</dd>
</dl>

<dl>
    <dd>Peyman Oreizy, Nenad Medvidovic, Richard N. Taylor, David
        S. Rosenblum. &quot;<strong>Software Architecture and
        Component Technologies: Bridging the Gap</strong>&quot;. <a
        href="http://www.objs.com/workshops/ws9801/index.html"><em>Proceedings
        of the OMG-DARPA Workshop on Compositional Software
        Architectures</em></a>, Monterey, CA, January 6-8, 1998.<br>
        Available in <a
        href="http://www.objs.com/workshops/ws9801/papers/paper007.pdf">Acrobat
        PDF</a>.</dd>
</dl>

<dl>
    <dd>Richard N. Taylor, Nenad Medvidovic, and Peyman Oreizy.
        &quot;<b>Architectural Implications of Common Operator
        Interfaces.</b>&quot; <i>Proceedings of the </i><a
        href="http://sunset.usc.edu/GSAW/GSAW98.html"><i>Ground
